DEFINITION: Indicator/Expression Unique ID. Created by combining: IND_UUID + IND_PER_CODE.
WHO Technical Unit indicator ID code (enabling mapping to historical datasets).
Temporal dimension value (e.g. 2020). Related to DIM_TIME_TYPE.
Temporal dimension type (e.g. Year). Related to DIM_TIME.
Geographic dimension code using M49 SDMX standard (e.g. 004). Related to DIM_GEO_CODE_TYPE.
Geographic dimension code type (e.g. "Country", "Region", "Global"). Related to DIM_GEO_CODE_M49.
Geographic dimension short name using WHO country, territory, and area reference list (e.g. Afghanistan). Related to DIM_GEO_CODE_M49.
Age dimension using SDMX age standard (e.g. Y_LT1).
Sex dimension using SDMX sex standard (e.g. FEMALE).
Degree of urbanization dimension using subset of SDMX urbanization standard, aligned to WHO application (e.g. URB)
Values as per unit of measure specified in variable name (e.g. Rate_Per_1000).
